# Telegram Changelog Notifications

## Auto-Trigger Rules

**Send Telegram notification when:**

### ✅ ALWAYS TRIGGER
- [x] User requests: "send changelog", "notify telegram", "update telegram bot"
- [x] Security vulnerabilities fixed
- [x] Breaking changes introduced
- [x] Major feature completed
- [x] Production deployment/version bump
- [x] Environment variables or secrets changed

### ❌ NEVER TRIGGER
- [ ] Minor fixes (typos, whitespace, formatting)
- [ ] Dev tooling changes (linters, configs)
- [ ] Comment updates only
- [ ] Test files (unless security-related)
- [ ] Temporary/debug code

## How to Send

Run this command with appropriate parameters:

```bash
node scripts/send-changelog.js --title "Title" --category "TYPE" --changes "Change 1\nChange 2"
```

**Categories:**
- `feature` ✨
- `fix` 🐛
- `security` 🔒
- `deployment` 🚀
- `breaking` ⚠️
- `performance` ⚡
- `refactor` ♻️

## Examples

**Security fix:**
```bash
node scripts/send-changelog.js --title "🔒 Security Patch" --category "security" --changes "Fixed CORS wildcard\nAdded request validation"
```

**New feature:**
```bash
node scripts/send-changelog.js --title "✨ AI Chat Feature" --category "feature" --changes "Added streaming chat endpoint\nImplemented token budget system\nAdded rate limiting"
```

**Deployment:**
```bash
node scripts/send-changelog.js --title "🚀 v2.0.0 Release" --category "deployment" --changes "Released to production\nMigrated database\nUpdated all dependencies"
```

## Format Rules

- Keep changes under 10 items
- Use action verbs: Added, Fixed, Removed, Updated
- Include file names when relevant
- Put security items first
- Use HTML format (not Markdown)
- Timezone: Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh
